metadata.name: DOOMKATS #170
metadata.description:
DOOMKATS have arrived, the favored cats of Death and the DOOMBUDS themselves. Join our feline army as we spread chaos across the world on our quest for treasure!

555 DOOMKATS will be ready to summon on Fx(hash). Included with it is a treasure hunt where you can get rewards straight from our prize pool by finding the matching set for each of your DOOMKATs.

DOOMKATS is a special collab between leftsilverhand x (the amazing) Vector Recite. Check out my profile for the roadmap and more information.

It is an Image composition made using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

If you find your treasure, you need to claim it here:
https://discord.gg/BCYcxFw5SF

Creators profiles:
https://twitter.com/leftsilverhand
https://twitter.com/vector_recite

metadata.name: DOS DELIGHT: ASCII #29
metadata.description:
As a child who encountered computers in the nostalgic era of the 90s, 'Dos Delight' stands as one of my most intimate generative art projects, bridging the gap between my early childhood and vivid memories intertwined with the world of computing.

In this generative art, I aim to recreate the aesthetics of 90s computers, tapping into the nostalgia of a bygone era. The algorithm, inspired by the playfulness of childhood, generates whimsical, childlike paintings reminiscent of a time when computers were new, and learning happened through wild exploration.

Designed to emulate the unrestrained creativity of a child at play, the algorithm produces artworks with pixelated charm, vibrant colors, and blocky shapesâ€”all rendered through the captivating lens of text aesthetics.

Press 4 or 8 to export in 4k and 8k in PNG.
Press 's' to export in screen resolution.

Murat Atimtay 2024 | @atimtay | https://www.atimtay.xyz

metadata.name: Maps of imagination #121
metadata.description:
"Maps of Imagination" is an abstract exploration of conventional cartography. 

It questions how we categorize and define the space around us. Maps can represent geographic reality, political regions, soil usage, and many other boundaries. But they are just a snapshot of one interpretation of reality.

To render at higher resolution, add &scale=2 (or 3, or 4) at the end of the url in live mode.

metadata.name: Garden of Lines #Rocks_Blooms #30
metadata.description:
"Rocks Blooms" captures the tranquility of a hidden garden, where vibrant flowers emerge gracefully from between resilient rocks, revealing a delicate balance between strength and fragility.

The number of layers is 9 layers
Size 1500 x 1500 pixels
Note: All layers and components are drawn separately by hand on the tablet

metadata.name: Miniscapes #353
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: Timing #497
metadata.description:
Time.. 
While one thing happens one time, another happens several times.

----------------------------------------------------------------
  Keys control:
    r: toggle rotation
    i: increment rotation speed
    d: decrement rotation speed
    p: toggle show points
    s: save current size image to .png
    x + 2/4/8: save 2x/4x/8x size image to .png
    1-9 + g: save 1-9 sec animation to .gif (depends on the machine resources)

  URL parameters:
    fps=<value>: frame rate
    r=true: rotation ON
    p=false: do not show points

metadata.name: cambi #163
metadata.description:
A gift for everyone to celebrate the birth of fxhash 2.0.

A small slice of the ultimate latent space, fashioned by time-loose voors.

Open edition for one year. Weakly dependant on the iteration number...

Press "s" to save image (or right-click-save) as 512x512 pixel png file.

metadata.name: Pixel Management #1080
metadata.description:
#tezpole has demonstrated to us all the importance of effective Cable Management. Intrigued by this challenge, I've delved deep into the pixels of this issue. ðŸ™‚

Drawing inspiration from Rev Dan Cattâ€™s 'Tally!' and applying similar principles of Cable Management, I've assembled a fun and free OE project.

This project dynamically evolves with each iteration.Grid is determined by a random value calculated as follows: the lower bound starts at 3 and increases incrementally with every 100 iterations, while the upper bound starts at 4 and increases with every 30 iterations. In practical terms, as the iteration count increases, both the minimum and maximum possible number of cols&rows gradually increase.

3200x3200px
Press [s] for .jpeg | Press [p] for .png
Made with p5.js

Rob Scalera | 2023
